post_text:
Reminder to Defiance Elementary parents of our staggered startup:

Monday, August 24 grades 2 and 3 will report. All other grades stay home.

Tuesday, August 25 grades 1 and 4 will report. All other grades stay home.

Wednesday, August 26 grades KinderStart and 5 will report. All other grades stay home.

Thursday, August 27 grades Kindergarten and our self-contained units will report. Grades 3-5 will also report. Grades KinderStart, 1 and 2 will stay home.

Friday, August 28 Grades KS-5 will be in session. All students report to school!

Monday, August 31 will be a Teacher Work Day to reevaluate our new COVID procedures and adjust accordingly.

We realize this can be an inconvenience to families; however, we feel this is the safest way to start school and teach our new protocols to each grade level. Thank you for your flexibility!

Thank you for your support of the 2020 Creative Writing Contest sponsored by Friends of the Defiance Public Library, Sylvan Learning, State Bank, and our many local prize donors.

Winners were:

Grades K-2
1st place - Vivian Zipfel, Grade 2, Defiance Elementary, Mrs. Hasselbring teacher

post_text: In light of recent action from the State of Ohio aimed to limit the spread of COVID-19, all Northwest Ohio Early Childhood Developmental Screenings have been postponed through the end of March. For those who have a scheduled appointment in March, you are asked to monitor the Northwest Ohio Early Childhood Developmental Screening facebook page and/or phone calls from area code 567 for further information as it becomes available. Scheduling for all future screenings is on hold for those who do not yet an appointment.

post_text:
FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE: December 7, 2019

Defiance City Schools has become aware of the criminal charges that have been filed against Solomon Garcia. Mr. Garcia was employed by RFS Charitable Foundation, T.A.C.K.L.E., Toledo, Ohio, an organization which has provided behavioral health services to the District. We have been informed by RFS, that they have terminated Mr.Garcia’s employment. He is no longer providing any services to students of the District and would not be permitted on District premises. Furthermore, we have suspended all services provided by RFS Charitable Foundation, T.A.C.K.L.E. The safety of our students is a top priority.

Respectfully,

Robert Morton, Superintendent

post_text:
ATTENTION PARENTS: This is a reminder for those parents that have not completed the online registration.
Defiance City Schools is utilizing an online student registration/data validation system for the this school year. The system is a secure and green process, which allows us to verify all student demographic, emergency and medical information for your child for new school year. This system will also allow families to electronically sign the annual permission forms as well as Emergency Medical forms needed for athletics and extracurricular activities.
The online registration can be found at Defiance City Schools - Central Registration
You have received one mailing on this and will receive one more IF YOU HAVE NOT COMPLETED THIS PROCESS. You can find general instructions by going to the Defiance City School website clicking on Central Registration - Returning Student Registration. (images shown below)

http://www.defiancecityschools.org/

post_text: Defiance Elementary News: Open House for students in grades 1-5 will be Tuesday, August 21 from 3:30-5:30 p.m. Kindergarten and KinderStart students will receive telephone calls from their classroom teachers regarding their orientation meeting date/time. Class lists for all other students will be posted on Friday, August 17. Our first day of school for grades 1-5 will be Wednesday, August 22. KinderStart will begin on Friday, August 24 and Kindergarten will begin on Monday, August 27. We look forward to seeing everyone in a few short weeks!

post_text: Four soon-to-be-sixth graders had the opportunity this week to participate in an Honors Choir as part of the Ohio Choral Directors Association Summer Conference. Dylan Johnson, Olivia Myers, Emma Tackett and Jacob Schnitkey were nominated by the 5th grade choir director, Jennifer Long to attend the 3 day program held on the campus of Otterbein University. The event culminated with a wonderful concert June 20. Congratulations to these students for an outstanding performance.
